Grammy-winning singer Burna Boy has reacted over news of his involvement in a shooting incident at a nightclub last week. The police on Sunday said Domini Ogulu would be invited for questioning over the shooting incident that occurred at Cubana Nightclub in Victoria Island. Policemen attached to the singer on Wednesday opened fire in the club following a disagreement with other clubbers. It was alleged that an argument ensued between Burna Boy and a man whose wife he allegedly made indecent advances to.   Second Republic politician Olaniyan dies at 92     Malabu Oil: We’re studying UK Court judgement –…     Presidency to Oyedepo: you’re blinded by hatred for…   Already, all five policemen have been arrested and detained on the instruction of the Inspector-General Alkali Usman. Following the incident and the police decision to call him in for questioning, the “Twice as Tall” singer has continued to top most social media discourse with many calling for his head and others making case in his defense. Reacting to his ‘crucifixion’ on social media, “Odogwu” said he won’t be shocked if the Nigerian users claimed he launched Boko Haram. “Nigerian Social media can say BURNA BOY started Boko haram, e no go shock me,” the singer tweeted.